Following instructions on <denchmark-link:http://deeplearning4j.org/gettingstarted#cli>http://deeplearning4j.org/gettingstarted#cli</denchmark-link>
 , I tried installing CLI on a OS X machine and got a SHA256 mismatch.
 OS: El Capitan
 Java 8
 Homebrew 0.9.9
 brew install homebrew/science/deeplearning4j-cli
 ==> Installing deeplearning4j-cli from homebrew/science
 ==> Downloading <denchmark-link:https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/skymind/bin/deeplearning4j-cli.tar.gz>https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/skymind/bin/deeplearning4j-cli.tar.gz</denchmark-link>
 
 <denchmark-h:h6>################################################################## 100.0%</denchmark-h>
 
 Error: SHA256 mismatch
 Expected: aaa664958f5d53570d02d75e7f61a491f5f75372d5721bf4f6c1efe31e971fcb
 Actual: b42451cf3c437fa648878b3fde07b7fd521997c0ae22568bb565a13efe00b7d0
 Archive: /Library/Caches/Homebrew/deeplearning4j-cli-0.4-rc3.8.tar.gz
 To retry an incomplete download, remove the file above.
